com.interpss.core.algo

Interface LfCalculator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LfCalculatorImpl

    public interface LfCalculator
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Lf Calculator'. Loadflow calculation implementation class

    The following features are supported:

    • Lf Algo
    • Nr Solver
    See Also:
    CoreAlgorithmPackage.getLfCalculator()

      • getLfAlgo

        LoadflowAlgorithm getLfAlgo()
        Returns the value of the 'Lf Algo' container reference. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Lf Calculator'.

        If the meaning of the 'Lf Algo' reference isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

        reference to the parent LF algorithm object, containing the object.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Lf Algo' container reference.
        See Also:
        setLfAlgo(LoadflowAlgorithm), CoreAlgorithmPackage.getLfCalculator_LfAlgo(), LoadflowAlgorithm.getLfCalculator()
